Long story…

As Christmas approached, my heart started to hurt real bad. This was the season my father enjoyed the most. 
When we were younger , my dad used to dress up like #santa and deliver gifts to his godchildren in his Cadillac first thing Christmas morning. 
My kids asked for the tree, they wanted both of the trees in our family room. How could I say no. So today I took my time (for the first time) all by myself and decorated. My back hurts real good and my heart feels so much better. I had to face this loss. I had so much anger attached to this. I’m letting it go. God would want me to. Daddy would want me to. I think I’ll sleep here tonight before my flight and praise God for His Son’s Birth. It’s the reason why, I’ll see my daddy again. 

Happy Holidays y’all 🎄🎄🎄🎄🎄

5 years ago I met this beautiful lady Dori. @ladydob3 Dori booked me to do her and her bridal party for the wedding. Then she added her husband @uriyahmd to my list! That was my first time doing bride and groom. 😍 (let me drop a pause iykyk 😜) I digress 😇. Since then I’ve been her #hairstylist and she’s been talking about loc’ing her hair. 2 months ago, we started the process. This process isn’t for the weak at heart. You can’t shampoo them often. Basically you have to look rough. Dori remembered she still had a bag of her husbands locs he had cut soon after the wedding. She asked if I did loc extensions and I said ,” what can’t I do! 😂😂😚😚🤪” let me stop 🫣
So it’s done! When her husband saw it, he said, “I don’t usually get to see the back of my head so this is awesome! “🤣 Then He said,” we look amazing! 😂” and last but definitely not least he said ,” you look good, I helped, You’re welcome 😎😝😝”. 

He had tears in his eyes and now officially I have added to my spiritual position of connecting a man and his wife! 

If this was a fun love story, drop some 🖤🖤🖤 In the comments 

Side note. One hiccup, after the locs were installed, we remembered we died his hair black 😩😩😩. So I’m going to hit her locs with a color correction next visit! 🥰
